ion":6,"text":"So, first, what causes leukocoria?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.35305,0.059561,0.059385,0.066261,0.063488,0.061371,0.057458,0.06184,0.061037,0.055523,0.057502,0.043519],"unified_progress":[0.2296,0.092836,0.071063,0.067519,0.078335,0.07281,0.083923,0.076302,0.070778,0.056567,0.051808,0.048462]},{"section":7,"text":"Well, the most common things I can think of are retinoblastoma, cataract, Coats' disease, maybe retinopathy of prematurity, but this kid is 2 years old, so ROP is less likely unless they were very premature.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.062834,0.12903,0.063878,0.10792,0.10651,0.10401,0.093308,0.083868,0.073564,0.067598,0.058693,0.048784],"unified_progress":[0.078814,0.10593,0.070257,0.1012,0.1008,0.10153,0.091488,0.089763,0.082329,0.07464,0.060116,0.043135]},{"section":8,"text":"But the key here is the retinal detachment and the ultrasound findings.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047938,0.092321,0.10561,0.10446,0.09958,0.092466,0.088697,0.082737,0.080723,0.077637,0.066642,0.061189],"unified_progress":[0.049867,0.078003,0.088333,0.099513,0.10088,0.097685,0.095491,0.091483,0.088796,0.084501,0.070126,0.055324]},{"section":9,"text":"The ultrasound B scan shows a heterogeneous subretinal mass with calcification.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040512,0.089419,0.10146,0.1056,0.10018,0.098839,0.093605,0.085315,0.091816,0.07274,0.063538,0.05698],"unified_progress":[0.038785,0.077671,0.097469,0.11731,0.11259,0.10458,0.099822,0.089821,0.089582,0.06923,0.055432,0.047707]},{"section":10,"text":"Calcification in the eye...","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.33545,0.056073,0.057133,0.064488,0.062472,0.063489,0.059147,0.066269,0.065747,0.059466,0.062671,0.047593],"unified_progress":[0.22203,0.085222,0.073052,0.070224,0.079475,0.074486,0.082205,0.079444,0.073132,0.057881,0.052356,0.050493]},{"section":11,"text":"Retinoblastoma often has calcifications.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041322,0.08999,0.063144,0.1098,0.11386,0.1072,0.10312,0.092019,0.081398,0.075195,0.065634,0.057321],"unified_progress":[0.045083,0.074826,0.067179,0.10417,0.10886,0.10547,0.10217,0.09936,0.091158,0.083366,0.067001,0.05136]},{"section":12,"text":"Let me recall.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32669,0.05234,0.05314,0.06416,0.063674,0.063965,0.060192,0.068017,0.069011,0.062638,0.066163,0.050006],"unified_progress":[0.21329,0.081188,0.066013,0.065076,0.074723,0.072653,0.10444,0.080041,0.076224,0.059851,0.05496,0.051544]},{"section":13,"text":"Retinoblastoma is a malignant tumor of the retina, usually in kids under 5.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046248,0.098634,0.059218,0.10497,0.11077,0.10797,0.10248,0.091885,0.081054,0.075186,0.065316,0.056267],"unified_progress":[0.059857,0.082833,0.064237,0.10007,0.10273,0.10446,0.098764,0.09807,0.090475,0.082823,0.065613,0.050078]},{"section":14,"text":"It presents with leukocoria, and on imaging, calcifications are common.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035232,0.07249,0.084431,0.094132,0.10102,0.10248,0.10267,0.095685,0.088281,0.088086,0.072367,0.063128],"unified_progress":[0.040184,0.064902,0.084664,0.093814,0.099279,0.10522,0.10185,0.099507,0.094652,0.088983,0.071733,0.055206]},{"section":15,"text":"The mass would be the tumor itself.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037711,0.079077,0.091151,0.097334,0.096838,0.096879,0.095948,0.090225,0.093228,0.081876,0.072567,0.067168],"unified_progress":[0.045307,0.070699,0.087229,0.099242,0.10346,0.10068,0.097965,0.09355,0.09383,0.080167,0.068767,0.059102]},{"section":16,"text":"Subretinal masses can cause retinal detachment because the tumor pushes on the retina.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036623,0.08089,0.09271,0.10022,0.099009,0.10012,0.097214,0.089724,0.095193,0.078864,0.068198,0.061236],"unified_progress":[0.039047,0.071908,0.092588,0.1072,0.11075,0.10623,0.10227,0.093478,0.092974,0.073724,0.059394,0.050432]},{"section":17,"text":"Other possibilities: Coat's disease is a vascular abnormality leading to retinal detachment, but it's usually unilateral and doesn't have calcifications.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026465,0.062132,0.07843,0.092619,0.10185,0.10478,0.10749,0.1014,0.094168,0.091107,0.076933,0.062632],"unified_progress":[0.029199,0.057886,0.079898,0.09341,0.099891,0.1218,0.10707,0.10266,0.096295,0.0906,0.070674,0.050621]},{"section":18,"text":"Cataract can cause leukocoria but wouldn't show a mass with calcification.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029847,0.066274,0.078754,0.087925,0.093416,0.098103,0.10169,0.099718,0.10001,0.09278,0.083471,0.068009],"unified_progress":[0.035063,0.063446,0.080349,0.091247,0.099597,0.10231,0.10193,0.10138,0.10005,0.094152,0.075688,0.054782]},{"section":19,"text":"Retinopathy of prematurity can cause retinal detachment but again, no calcifications.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025914,0.059444,0.073735,0.085892,0.094675,0.10027,0.10498,0.10322,0.10068,0.096709,0.085824,0.06866],"unified_progress":[0.032245,0.059393,0.077698,0.088919,0.097334,0.10569,0.10357,0.10398,0.10108,0.09707,0.078236,0.054785]},{"section":20,"text":"So the calcification is a big clue here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032598,0.071357,0.089944,0.095702,0.094255,0.089856,0.090416,0.088231,0.087424,0.092292,0.082265,0.085661],"unified_progress":[0.034381,0.062142,0.075071,0.087536,0.090895,0.092139,0.097183,0.095069,0.09423,0.097502,0.090697,0.083154]},{"section":21,"text":"Also, the age is spot-on for retinoblastoma.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040468,0.075387,0.086041,0.091357,0.092549,0.092058,0.090768,0.08912,0.087218,0.089406,0.082024,0.083602],"unified_progress":[0.054865,0.071623,0.077147,0.083379,0.086485,0.089916,0.090867,0.092726,0.091421,0.091943,0.087862,0.081766]},{"section":22,"text":"The combination of leukocoria, retinal detachment, and a subretinal mass with calcifications on ultrasound points strongly to retinoblastoma.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033996,0.069195,0.080521,0.087417,0.090266,0.092339,0.093672,0.091261,0.096267,0.090953,0.087672,0.086439],"unified_progress":[0.038645,0.060659,0.075671,0.086239,0.091912,0.095985,0.095738,0.095419,0.098449,0.093271,0.08808,0.079931]},{"section":23,"text":"I should also consider other tumors, but in a child this age, retinoblastoma is the top differential.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032078,0.064629,0.077904,0.084446,0.087189,0.088016,0.090057,0.090249,0.091054,0.095418,0.091442,0.10752],"unified_progress":[0.039552,0.059389,0.067608,0.075882,0.079862,0.085341,0.087792,0.093293,0.095664,0.09941,0.10487,0.11134]},{"section":24,"text":"The calcification is a key feature that helps differentiate it from other causes.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030455,0.065673,0.081882,0.088658,0.089911,0.088829,0.091349,0.090647,0.091893,0.094807,0.090095,0.095802],"unified_progress":[0.031707,0.055318,0.068072,0.079608,0.084184,0.088295,0.092045,0.094938,0.098328,0.10328,0.10274,0.10149]},{"section":25,"text":"So yeah, the most likely diagnosis is retinoblastoma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025065,0.048001,0.056877,0.063558,0.070091,0.076041,0.082605,0.087685,0.096209,0.10054,0.11446,0.17887],"unified_progress":[0.023629,0.033078,0.040929,0.050193,0.05577,0.067459,0.072082,0.084917,0.098435,0.11018,0.15255,0.21078]},{"section":26,"text":"<answer> Retinoblastoma </answer>","dimension":7,"group":0,"